※※
# delete-sky-workflow

Manually-run workflow that finds a `.sky` workflow by name and deletes it,
behind a manual approval gate. Pure bash + a wait — no LLM tokens. Flow:

  (manual run: --var dir, name)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  not found ──▶ list <dir> + stop
   │  find  │
   └────────┘
       │ found
       ▼
   ┌─────────┐  reject ──▶ stop (file kept)
   │ confirm │  ⏸ manual approval gate (timeout 1h)
   └─────────┘
       │ approve
       ▼
   ┌────────┐
   │ remove │ ── rm <dir>/<name>.sky
   └────────┘
       │
       ▼
     done

Run it (state where the workflow lives with --var dir):

  skyway run delete-sky-workflow --var dir=".sky/workflows" --var name="old-workflow"

  - dir   directory the workflow lives in — STATE THIS before running (e.g. .sky/workflows)
  - name  kebab-case filename of the workflow to delete (no .sky extension)
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "delete-sky-workflow"
description = "Find a .sky workflow by name and delete it behind a manual approval gate. Fire via: skyway run delete-sky-workflow --var dir=<dir> --var name=<file>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※find※
Locate workflow by name; exit non-zero if not found, halting the run.
No dependencies. Resolves {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky.
※※

§find§
bash_file = "./scripts/find.sh"
§§

※confirm※
Manual approval gate: human confirms deletion (irreversible action).
depends_on: find. wait.channel=manual, timeout=1h, prompt=delete {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky.
※※

§confirm§
depends_on = ["find"]
wait.prompt = "Delete {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky? Approve to remove it, reject to keep."
wait.channel = "manual"
wait.timeout = "1h"
§§

※remove※
Delete the workflow file after approval.
depends_on: confirm. Executes rm {{dir}}/{{name}}.sky.
※※

§remove§
depends_on = ["confirm"]
bash_file = "./scripts/remove.sh"
§§
